LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION NO. 2
BY RUBEL
1 A JOINT RESOLUTION
2 PROPOSING AN AMENDMENT TO THE CONSTITUTION OF THE STATE OF IDAHO RELATING TO
3 MARRIAGE; REPEALING SECTION 28, ARTICLE III OF THE CONSTITUTION OF THE
4 STATE OF IDAHO, RELATING TO MARRIAGE; STATING THE QUESTION TO BE SUBMIT-
5 TED TO THE ELECTORATE; DIRECTING THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL TO PREPARE THE
6 STATEMENTS REQUIRED BY LAW; AND DIRECTING THE SECRETARY OF STATE TO PUB-
7 LISH THE AMENDMENT AND ARGUMENTS AS REQUIRED BY LAW.
8 Be It Resolved by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
9 SECTION 1. That Section 28, Article III of the Constitution of the
10 State of Idaho, be, and the same is hereby repealed.
11 SECTION 2. The question to be submitted to the electors of the State of
12 Idaho at the next general election shall be as follows:
13 "Shall Section 28, Article III of the Constitution of the State of Idaho
14 prohibiting same sex marriage be repealed?"
15 SECTION 3. The Legislative Council is directed to prepare the state-
16 ments required by Section 67-453, Idaho Code, and file the same.
17 SECTION 4. The Secretary of State is hereby directed to publish this
18 proposed constitutional amendment and arguments as required by law.

